			<description><![CDATA[Kavitaverma: To change our deep rooted sanskars we need determination, attention and patience.  Deep rooted sanskars have become natural to the soul and so automatically come into play when responding or reacting to situations, relationships or even our own thoughts.  We have to become a detached observer of ourselves so we can really 'see' what the root of the sanskara is and make the concious choice to change - to choose the ascending path, rather than slide down the decending path of habit. To cultivate pure awareness and to receive power - meditation and connection to the Supreme Source of all powers and qualities; God the Purifier - is a direct way to change sanskaras.  With this focused attention and direct relationship the soul becomes pure.]]></description>
